---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Details from "../components/ui/Details.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Details Component Demo"
    description="Demo page showcasing the Details.astro collapsible component in FAQ style."
>
    <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">
            Details Component Demo
        </h1>
        <p class="mb-10 text-center text-gray-600">
            Below are some frequently asked questions using the <code
                >Details.astro</code
            > collapsible panel component.
        </p>
        <section class="space-y-6">
            <Details open={true}>
                <span slot="heading">What is PBV?</span>
                <p>
                    PBV stands for "Project Based Ventures." We focus on
                    hands-on learning and innovation, nurturing young minds and
                    fostering a love for learning.
                </p>
            </Details>
            <Details>
                <span slot="heading">How does the Details component work?</span>
                <p>
                    The Details component provides an accessible, animated
                    collapsible panel. Click the heading to expand or collapse
                    the content. Plus and minus icons indicate the state.
                </p>
            </Details>
            <Details>
                <span slot="heading">Can I use multiple panels on a page?</span>
                <p>
                    Yes! You can use as many <code>&lt;Details&gt;</code> components
                    as you like, each with its own heading and content.
                </p>
            </Details>
            <Details>
                <span slot="heading">Is it accessible?</span>
                <p>
                    Yes, the component uses ARIA attributes and keyboard
                    navigation for accessibility.
                </p>
            </Details>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
